All of that should happen as you describe. Unfortunately, campus purchased a peoplesoft system and it slows everything down tremendously.  

There are 20 spaces in the class and 247 students on the waitlist. That means the overwhelming majority of students on the waitlist will not be able to take the class this semester.  Some students currently enrolled will drop but it is still unlikely that more than 40-75 students currently on the waitlist will be able to be enrolled.  To be enrolled you will need there to be space both in the lecture and discussion section for which you are waitlisted.   I will process the online forms for conflicts with CS188 tomorrow (Tuesday) as well as pay special attention to double-majors but if there is no availability in the sections you have chosen that will not be of significant use.   Starting Wednesday morning, non-majors will be enrolled in order of waitlist so CS/EECS majors receiving this will need to make sure they are waitlisted for open sections asap if they wish that priority to be useful.
